# UniFi Site Manager API Client

Python interface for interacting with UniFiâ€™s Site Manager Integration API. Tested on selfhosted local instance only.

## ğŸ“¦ Usage

```python
from unifi_sm_api.api import SiteManagerAPI

api = SiteManagerAPI(
    api_key="fakeApiKey1234567890",
    base_url="https://192.168.100.1/proxy/network/integration/",
    version="v1",
    verify_ssl=False
)

sites = api.get_sites()
devices = api.get_unifi_devices(site_id="site-id")
clients = api.get_clients(site_id="site-id")
```

---

## ğŸ“˜ Endpoints Covered

- `/sites` â€” list available sites
- `/sites/{site_id}/devices` â€” list UniFi devices for a site
- `/sites/{site_id}/clients` â€” list connected clients

## ğŸ”§ Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- `requests`
- `pytest` (for running tests)
